<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">
After examination of the remaining specimens from the Say and Harris collections at the Museum of Comparative Zoology, no appropriate specimens were located for 
<typeStatus box="[709,807,256,279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation. A male specimen from the LeConte and Horn collection (
<collectionCode box="[271,334,290,313]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33791" name="Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">MCZ</collectionCode>
), collected from near the original 
<typeStatus box="[702,748,290,313]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">type</typeStatus>
locality of “eastern 
<collectingRegion box="[969,1071,290,313]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">Colorado</collectingRegion>
, near the Rocky Mountains”, was chosen as a suitable replacement. The specimen represents the typical phenotype for the species from the original 
<typeStatus box="[1390,1436,325,348]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">type</typeStatus>
locality. Future revisionary work in this genus may result in additional closely related cryptic taxa discovered elsewhere across the current widespread range of 
<taxonomicName box="[577,728,393,417]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cercus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallipennis">
<emphasis box="[577,728,393,417]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">N. pallipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Labels for the newly designated specimen are as follows: “Col” “Horn Coll/H3673” “ 
<collectionCode box="[379,439,429,452]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33791" name="Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">MCZ</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[447,501,429,452]" country="Uganda" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13589" name="Ministry of Natural Resources" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">ENT</collectionCode>
/00596673”. Red label added reads as follows: “ 
<typeStatus box="[1016,1108,429,452]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295">Neotype</typeStatus>
/ 
<taxonomicName box="[1116,1316,429,452]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cercus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallipennis">Cercus pallipennis</taxonomicName>
/ 
<bibRefCitation author="Say" box="[1324,1427,429,452]" pageId="2" pageNumber="295" refString="Say, T. (1823) Descriptions of coleopterous insects collected in the late expedition to the Rocky Mountains, performed by order of Mr. Calhoun, Secretary of War, under the command of Major Long. Journal of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 3 (1), 139 - 331." type="journal article" year="1823">Say, 1823</bibRefCitation>
/ Designated by Powell &amp; Cline 2016”.
</paragraph>
